2
00:02:11,800 --> 00:02:14,300
わー〜
Wah~

3
00:02:15,900 --> 00:02:22,500
Good morning, afternoon, evening...

4
00:02:23,500 --> 00:02:29,000
It is Tako Time. What is this?

5
00:02:33,800 --> 00:02:35,000
あ...
Oh...

6
00:02:44,200 --> 00:02:47,000
アリーナで... バトルダンジョン...
Arena... Battle dungeon...

7
00:02:49,000 --> 00:02:53,000
Oh, daily quests. Right.

8
00:02:53,500 --> 00:02:55,300
はぁ...
Oh...

9
00:02:58,500 --> 00:03:00,500
あれ？
Huh?

10
00:03:05,100 --> 00:03:09,500
It seems I'm out of bees.

11
00:03:13,200 --> 00:03:15,000
I can fix that.

12
00:03:17,000 --> 00:03:20,000
I'm just going to put a whole bunch of bees...

13
00:03:21,500 --> 00:03:23,500
...in here.

14
00:03:25,500 --> 00:03:30,000
It cannot be... Sorry about the beep today.

15
00:03:36,500 --> 00:03:39,000
So many!

16
00:03:40,000 --> 00:03:43,000
Oh, there're a few in there too.

17
00:03:51,500 --> 00:03:56,500
な、な、な...
Na, na, na...

18
00:03:59,000 --> 00:04:04,500
Oh, I should've put like Shulkers or something so they can... they can figure it out themselves.

19
00:04:08,500 --> 00:04:10,000
Oh, more bees.

20
00:04:14,000 --> 00:04:16,000
I can sell some of the bees.

21
00:04:19,500 --> 00:04:22,500
た、た、た...
Ta, ta, ta...

22
00:04:26,500 --> 00:04:29,500
Yeah, there's no purple, okay, so...

23
00:04:36,000 --> 00:04:38,200
Ah, it doesn't matter.

24
00:04:41,000 --> 00:04:44,500
This isn't our number one source of money, anyway.

25
00:04:50,000 --> 00:04:54,000
Okay, okay, okay, it's fine, it's fine.

26
00:04:57,500 --> 00:04:59,000
Because...

27
00:05:00,308 --> 00:05:01,308
Although,

28
00:05:04,208 --> 00:05:05,508
we may have...

29
00:05:07,408 --> 00:05:08,808
...gotten a slight nerf...

30
00:05:08,808 --> 00:05:11,808
...to the money we earn by harvesting.

31
00:05:12,808 --> 00:05:14,308
I think 18 million...

32
00:05:14,308 --> 00:05:16,808
...is still within the grasp.

33
00:05:17,608 --> 00:05:20,108
A slight nerf, I should say.

34
00:05:25,308 --> 00:05:28,108
But with the amount we earned yesterday,

35
00:05:28,108 --> 00:05:30,908
I feel like...

36
00:05:30,908 --> 00:05:32,808
...we can earn a fraction of that today.

37
00:05:33,608 --> 00:05:36,508
It won't be a prob...

38
00:05:42,508 --> 00:05:44,708
But we got to be careful,

39
00:05:45,308 --> 00:05:46,808
because...

40
00:05:47,408 --> 00:05:48,808
...we don't have any...

41
00:05:48,808 --> 00:05:50,808
...limits to stonks today,

42
00:05:51,108 --> 00:05:53,608
which means I have to zero out...

43
00:05:53,608 --> 00:05:55,308
...and sell...

44
00:05:56,508 --> 00:05:58,208
...the stonks.

45
00:06:03,408 --> 00:06:05,108
Cause they're gonna...

46
00:06:05,108 --> 00:06:08,308
...sell automatically if I forget about them,

47
00:06:08,308 --> 00:06:11,508
and it's gonna mess up our plan.

48
00:06:18,008 --> 00:06:21,008
So at the first sighting of an increase,

49
00:06:21,008 --> 00:06:24,408
we shall sell the remaining stonks,

50
00:06:25,508 --> 00:06:28,508
and just forget about it.

51
00:06:31,908 --> 00:06:34,508
Oh, yeah, we have five more extra...

52
00:06:34,508 --> 00:06:35,808
...what-cha-ma-call-it...

53
00:06:35,808 --> 00:06:38,208
...points today, which means...

54
00:06:38,208 --> 00:06:41,408
...that if I finish getting the... wait,

55
00:06:41,408 --> 00:06:45,208
but then I'll get money from doing the extra stuff.

56
00:06:49,808 --> 00:06:51,508
That can't do.

57
00:06:56,208 --> 00:06:59,708
Okay, I'll gather the rest and go sell.

58
00:07:11,208 --> 00:07:13,508
I will make sure I don't get sidetracked from my goal.

59
00:07:23,508 --> 00:07:25,808
Why not sell it at the lowest right now and sell later?

60
00:07:25,808 --> 00:07:27,008
Because...

61
00:07:30,808 --> 00:07:33,408
...I'm not too fond of uncertainties.

62
00:07:48,508 --> 00:07:51,208
Three raids and only plus?

63
00:07:53,508 --> 00:07:55,708
Is that what they said?

64
00:07:59,308 --> 00:08:02,308
But the unknown is scary.

65
00:08:05,108 --> 00:08:09,508
I mean, they did say the server's gonna be open a little bit after midnight,

66
00:08:09,508 --> 00:08:13,108
so if I'm not feeling completely dead,

67
00:08:13,108 --> 00:08:15,508
maybe we can do like a mini-game or something.

68
00:08:15,508 --> 00:08:19,408
But high chance I'm gonna be dead because I went outside today,

69
00:08:19,408 --> 00:08:22,508
and every time I go outside it means...

70
00:08:22,508 --> 00:08:24,408
...I feel dead!

71
00:08:25,508 --> 00:08:28,008
My stamina's running a little low today.

72
00:08:48,008 --> 00:08:51,208
Yeah. I mean, I think I did my best,

73
00:08:52,508 --> 00:08:56,008
participating in the event.

74
00:08:56,508 --> 00:08:58,508
I had fun.

75
00:09:02,008 --> 00:09:04,108
I got good food today.

76
00:09:06,508 --> 00:09:10,008
I hung out with Biboo all day.

77
00:09:10,008 --> 00:09:12,508
Biboonium has been recharged!

78
00:09:33,508 --> 00:09:35,508
I did remember to headpat her.

79
00:09:35,508 --> 00:09:39,108
Of course I won't forget. It's like the first thing I do when I meet her.

80
00:09:46,508 --> 00:09:50,008
I have to say, we definitely aren't getting as much money as before, I feel.

81
00:09:51,508 --> 00:09:54,508
But a couple of rounds and I think...

82
00:09:54,508 --> 00:09:59,008
...we probably will.

83
00:10:00,316 --> 00:10:01,316
I mean...

84
00:10:01,316 --> 00:10:05,116
I mean, we're already like more than halfway to 1 million, so...

85
00:10:05,416 --> 00:10:09,316
...it's not too bad. Had a good, good head start yesterday.

86
00:10:19,016 --> 00:10:22,516
That feels like more than 25%.

87
00:10:25,516 --> 00:10:28,516
That's what it is, though, but like...

88
00:10:28,516 --> 00:10:34,616
percentages always feel weird because it's percentages, it's chance.

89
00:10:39,916 --> 00:10:46,016
Chance has always been wonky. Sometimes, because...

90
00:10:46,216 --> 00:10:52,216
...it just means it's not 100% of the time if it's not 100% of the times, you know?

91
00:10:58,716 --> 00:11:08,516
Ina of the Mountain's cool today: "If it's not 100%, it's not 100% of the time."

92
00:11:09,516 --> 00:11:13,216
My bees are equipped, always.

93
00:11:13,816 --> 00:11:19,416
I know they're equipped because I'm too lazy to change them.

94
00:11:20,916 --> 00:11:23,916
やまのいな〜
Yama no Ina~

95
00:11:26,516 --> 00:11:28,216
Speaking of which...

96
00:11:28,216 --> 00:11:33,016
I was recently craving some really peppery wings.

97
00:11:33,216 --> 00:11:38,216
And I remembered the wings I had when I went to Nagoya once.

98
00:11:38,616 --> 00:11:42,316
What was it? Sekai no Yamachan.

99
00:11:42,316 --> 00:11:48,316
I talked about it before, I think, but I really like their peppery wings. It's so yummy.

100
00:11:58,516 --> 00:12:01,216
Ah, my bag is full.

101
00:12:04,016 --> 00:12:07,516
世界の山ちゃん美味しいよね。
Sekai no Yamachan is tasty, isn't it?

102
00:12:13,016 --> 00:12:16,016
なんか最近食べたくなって...
Like, I've been craving them lately...

103
00:12:19,516 --> 00:12:22,016
...and I opened Uber...

104
00:12:25,516 --> 00:12:30,016
and I thought, "Wait, isn't there a Sekai no Yamachan nearby?"

105
00:12:32,016 --> 00:12:35,016
...but when I looked at the time, it was morning...

106
00:12:35,416 --> 00:12:38,416
朝、４時くらい。
Around 4 AM.

107
00:12:41,816 --> 00:12:44,816
あ、そっか。
Ah, right.

108
00:12:46,516 --> 00:12:49,016
4 AM in the morning.

109
00:12:49,016 --> 00:12:53,016
I wanted to eat the wings out of nowhere.

110
00:12:53,016 --> 00:13:00,216
So I was like, "Oh, is there like a Sekai no Yamachan nearby?" So I opened Uber.

111
00:13:00,216 --> 00:13:05,116
And there was not, and I was like, "Is there none near me that deliver?"

112
00:13:05,116 --> 00:13:10,016
And then I checked the time, and it was like 4:00 AM...

113
00:13:10,016 --> 00:13:16,816
...in the morning! I was like, "Oh, of course they're not open."

114
00:13:26,516 --> 00:13:31,016
But like, like if you just eat the wings, it's like really...

115
00:13:32,316 --> 00:13:37,816
...because I usually order it with like extra pepper sauce, right?

116
00:13:37,816 --> 00:13:45,016
So if I eat, eat the wings by themselves, it's really salty, but then...

117
00:13:45,016 --> 00:13:47,816
...I heat up...

118
00:13:49,016 --> 00:13:54,016
...some rice. Fresh, hot rice.

119
00:13:54,016 --> 00:13:59,016
And then I take a bite of the wings with the rice, and oh...

120
00:13:59,016 --> 00:14:01,316
...perfection.

121
00:14:07,516 --> 00:14:11,016
Truly. Truly.

122
00:14:15,016 --> 00:14:18,016
Yamachan's wings are... eh?

123
00:14:18,216 --> 00:14:21,016
いや、山ちゃん辛いぞ。
No, "Yamachan is spicy"...

124
00:14:21,016 --> 00:14:25,016
いなは言えないんですよ。
...is something Ina can't say.

125
00:14:35,216 --> 00:14:40,016
They're like, "Sekai no Yamachan is really spicy." I was like, "Eh?"

126
00:14:48,016 --> 00:14:51,016
え、辛くないんだわ。
Eh? They're not spicy.

127
00:15:00,624 --> 00:15:01,324
サンタ？
Santa?

128
00:15:01,324 --> 00:15:02,524
サンタ？
Santa?

129
00:15:02,524 --> 00:15:03,824
サンタ？
Santa?

130
00:15:03,824 --> 00:15:05,124
ほうほうほう
Ho, ho, ho!

131
00:15:05,124 --> 00:15:09,124
サンタ！久しぶり！
Santa! It's been a while!

132
00:15:09,124 --> 00:15:11,124
久しぶり！見て！
Long time no see! Look!

133
00:15:11,124 --> 00:15:13,024
あっ！
Ah!

134
00:15:13,024 --> 00:15:15,024
あー！タコダチ！
Ah! Takodachi!

135
00:15:15,024 --> 00:15:17,324
ここにも飾っておくよ
I'll display one here too!

136
00:15:17,324 --> 00:15:19,324
ありがとう、サンタ！
Thank you, Santa!

137
00:15:19,324 --> 00:15:20,524
サンタ！
Santa!

138
00:15:20,524 --> 00:15:22,324
ほうほうほう
Ho, ho, ho!

139
00:15:22,324 --> 00:15:25,524
ほうほうほう
Ho, ho, ho!

140
00:15:27,024 --> 00:15:32,024
タコダチ...
Takodachi...

141
00:15:36,024 --> 00:15:43,024
Why are you standing up though? Aren't you... aren't... aren't you an item? Aren't you supposed to be lying down?

142
00:15:43,024 --> 00:15:46,024
Well, I'm not against it.

143
00:15:55,024 --> 00:16:04,524
なんか、ししろんが「アイテム交換しないように、開けるの禁止です」と言ったとき、
You know, when Shishiron said, "To prevent item trading, opening them is prohibited,"

144
00:16:04,524 --> 00:16:13,024
あ、サンタのプレゼントももらえないと思ったんですけど。
I thought, "Ah, I won't be able to get presents from Santa anymore."

145
00:16:15,024 --> 00:16:19,024
そうですね、サンタって最初から、
But then, Santa from the start...

146
00:16:19,024 --> 00:16:34,024
私が見てないところにプレゼントを置いていくのがサンタの仕事。
leaving presents where I'm not looking is Santa's job.

147
00:16:34,024 --> 00:16:43,024
You know, when... when Shishiron said you're not supposed to give free items to people,

148
00:16:43,024 --> 00:16:47,524
I was like, "Oh, Santa can't give me another present anymore?"

149
00:16:47,524 --> 00:16:54,024
But then I realized, it is actually Santa's job to give presents when I'm not looking.

150
00:17:01,024 --> 00:17:04,024
Ho, ho, ho!

151
00:17:30,024 --> 00:17:33,024
Today is the last day of this event.

152
00:17:40,024 --> 00:17:49,024
いや、このタコダチ、ホロ鯖にもあったらいいな。
Man, I wish this Takodachi was on the Holo Server too.

153
00:17:49,024 --> 00:17:51,524
欲しい。
I want it.

154
00:17:51,524 --> 00:18:00,024
でもホロ鯖は、なんかカスタムのアイテムあんまりないから...
But the Holo Server doesn't really have custom items, so...

155
00:18:00,024 --> 00:18:08,524
いや、でもメンバーのマスコットくらいは大丈夫...大丈夫...大丈夫じゃないですか？運営さん？
No, but at least the members' mascots should be okay... right, managers?

156
00:18:08,524 --> 00:18:17,024
I want the mascots in the Holo Server. But then, Holo Server doesn't have that many custom items, but then it's the members' mascots, so you know...

157
00:18:17,024 --> 00:18:20,524
You know?

158
00:18:20,524 --> 00:18:27,524
Maybe they can make an exception?

159
00:18:42,024 --> 00:18:52,024
いや、でも今考えたら、なんかメンバーの頭とかあったっけ？ホロ鯖に。
But thinking about it now, did we have members' heads on the Holo Server?

160
00:18:52,024 --> 00:18:57,024
We do have the heads of the members and stuff, right? In the Holo Server.

161
00:18:57,024 --> 00:19:00,024
あった気がする。
I feel like we had them.

162
00:19:09,024 --> 00:19:24,024
あ、でも、なんかマスコットは...まあ、作るために、お金かかるかもね。
Ah, but maybe mascots... well, to make them, it might cost money.

163
00:19:24,024 --> 00:19:35,024
いや、でもなんか、持って帰ったらいいなと。
But, still, it'd be nice to take them home.

164
00:19:35,024 --> 00:19:47,024
It would be nice to carry it back, but of course it takes the golden coins to create these assets.

165
00:20:00,032 --> 00:20:01,432
been dirt.

166
00:20:01,432 --> 00:20:04,232
I don't know if they're still better though. But,

167
00:20:05,132 --> 00:20:06,332
watermelon.

168
00:20:07,132 --> 00:20:08,532
watermelon.

169
00:20:09,132 --> 00:20:10,532
I can't stop now.

170
00:20:10,532 --> 00:20:13,432
It's like, it's like too late to stop.

171
00:20:15,132 --> 00:20:17,332
I've committed.

172
00:20:35,832 --> 00:20:38,832
や、でももうすぐいけるじゃん？
But we can get there soon, right?

173
00:20:40,332 --> 00:20:42,532
We're already at 1.3 mil.

174
00:20:46,432 --> 00:20:48,332
I believe, I believe...

175
00:20:49,032 --> 00:20:52,332
You know, we thought 18 million wasn't doable, so we're aiming for 1.8.

176
00:20:53,432 --> 00:20:55,232
But it's going to work.

177
00:21:20,132 --> 00:21:23,232
So, my goal currently is to have...

178
00:21:23,232 --> 00:21:26,532
1-8-1-8-1-8-1-8 yen...

179
00:21:28,532 --> 00:21:30,832
at the very end.

180
00:21:58,732 --> 00:22:01,332
Yeah...

181
00:22:01,332 --> 00:22:04,232
arigatai English.
thankful for the English.

182
00:22:08,232 --> 00:22:11,232
So, I went to eat with Bibo today.

183
00:22:12,732 --> 00:22:15,532
Usually, I don't think I go out like...

184
00:22:15,532 --> 00:22:18,032
one-on-one with her that often.

185
00:22:18,032 --> 00:22:21,032
So, we usually have at least like one member who is very...

186
00:22:21,532 --> 00:22:22,532
who is more...

187
00:22:22,532 --> 00:22:25,532
Japanese pera pera, you know.
fluent in Japanese, you know.

188
00:22:25,632 --> 00:22:26,832
Oh no!

189
00:22:28,932 --> 00:22:31,032
So whenever we order,

190
00:22:31,532 --> 00:22:34,532
we would stare at them with glittering eyes,

191
00:22:39,132 --> 00:22:41,032
and be like,

192
00:22:41,032 --> 00:22:42,532
I want this.

193
00:22:45,132 --> 00:22:46,532
I want this.

194
00:22:48,332 --> 00:22:51,032
And we would have an ordering person.

195
00:22:55,232 --> 00:22:59,032
But this time, it was just me and Bibo,

196
00:22:59,032 --> 00:23:01,532
so of course, I was that role,

197
00:23:01,532 --> 00:23:04,532
except I can't read.

198
00:23:09,132 --> 00:23:10,532
So, as...

199
00:23:11,832 --> 00:23:12,832
as...

200
00:23:13,232 --> 00:23:14,632
naturally as...

201
00:23:15,132 --> 00:23:16,832
naturally as possible,

202
00:23:18,432 --> 00:23:21,032
I point to the menu and I go, "kore".
I point to the menu and I go, "this".

203
00:23:22,632 --> 00:23:24,532
hitotsu.
One.

204
00:23:30,232 --> 00:23:32,432
18？ はい、すみません...
18? Yes, sorry...

205
00:23:32,432 --> 00:23:35,032
そんなそんな甘い考えは無理でした。
Such, such naive thinking was impossible.

206
00:23:35,032 --> 00:23:36,532
えーっと...
Let's see...

207
00:23:37,032 --> 00:23:40,032
あっ、お金もない... え、インベントリ空きが... あっ...
Ah, no money... eh, the inventory space is... ah...

208
00:23:40,032 --> 00:23:41,232
あほ？
Idiot?

209
00:23:41,232 --> 00:23:42,532
あほ。
Idiot.

210
00:23:45,332 --> 00:23:47,332
And then I point to the next thing,

211
00:23:47,832 --> 00:23:49,032
and go, "kore".
and go, "this".

212
00:24:04,432 --> 00:24:06,132
うーん、ビーツ？
Hmm, beetroot?

213
00:24:06,132 --> 00:24:07,532
あ、ほんまや！
Ah, you're right!

214
00:24:08,532 --> 00:24:10,532
これ買おう！
Let's buy this!

215
00:24:13,232 --> 00:24:15,032
うわーー！何これ？
Whoa! What is this?

216
00:24:15,032 --> 00:24:16,832
回転...？
Spinning...?

217
00:24:41,532 --> 00:24:44,232
絹豆腐こ先輩がやってたウィザーのあれか...
Is this the Wither thing that Kinudofuko-senpai was doing?

218
00:24:44,232 --> 00:24:47,532
