It's running!

1108
02:11:50,385 --> 02:11:53,385
あとちょっとなんだ！
Just a little more!

1109
02:11:53,385 --> 02:11:56,385
いけ、いけ、いけ、いけ！
Go, go, go, go!

1110
02:11:56,385 --> 02:11:59,385
なぐれ！なぐれ！
Punch it! Punch it!

1111
02:11:59,385 --> 02:12:04,385
うわああ！
Whoaaa!

1112
02:12:04,385 --> 02:12:09,885
いけいけいけいけ！
Go, go, go, go!

1113
02:12:09,885 --> 02:12:13,885
あとちょっと！
Almost there!

1114
02:12:13,885 --> 02:12:17,885
やったー！
We did it!

1115
02:12:17,885 --> 02:12:21,885
よかったー！おめでとうございます！
Thank goodness! Congratulations!

1116
02:12:21,885 --> 02:12:26,385
おめでとうございます！
Congratulations!

1117
02:12:26,385 --> 02:12:28,885
これですっきりやね。
What a relief.

1118
02:12:28,885 --> 02:12:31,885
守られましたね！
We were protected!

1119
02:12:31,885 --> 02:12:34,385
パチパチパチパチ。
(Clapping)

1120
02:12:34,385 --> 02:12:37,885
守られました！
We protected it!

1121
02:12:37,885 --> 02:12:40,885
それではルーレットを...
Now, let's spin the roulette...

1122
02:12:40,885 --> 02:12:43,885
これは...何？
What is... this?

1123
02:12:43,885 --> 02:12:46,885
これはルーレット...
This is the roulette...

1124
02:12:46,885 --> 02:12:49,385
おめでとうございます。
Congratulations.

1125
02:12:49,385 --> 02:12:52,385
カブカブカブ...
Stocks, stocks, stocks...

1126
02:12:52,385 --> 02:12:55,885
よろしくお願いします。
Please look forward to it.

1127
02:12:55,885 --> 02:12:57,885
え？2円？
Eh? 2 yen?

1128
02:12:57,885 --> 02:12:59,885
2円しかない。素晴らしい！
Only 2 yen. Wonderful!

1129
02:12:59,885 --> 02:13:02,885
カブどうなんだろう？
How will the stocks go?

1130
02:13:02,885 --> 02:13:06,385
頼む、頼む！
Please, please!

1131
02:13:06,385 --> 02:13:08,885
カブしか持ってない。
I only have stocks.

1132
02:13:08,885 --> 02:13:12,885
やばい、プラスこれ...
Oh no, plus this...

1133
02:13:12,885 --> 02:13:16,885
ししろフード、プラス500円！おめでとうございます！
Shishiro Foods, plus 500 yen! Congratulations!

1134
02:13:16,885 --> 02:13:19,385
え、ししろフード... 500！
Eh, Shishiro Foods... 500!

1135
02:13:19,385 --> 02:13:23,385
やることしかないじゃん！
There's nothing else to do!

1136
02:13:23,385 --> 02:13:26,885
泥棒建設、プラス200円！
Dorobou Construction, plus 200 yen!

1137
02:13:26,885 --> 02:13:29,885
おめでとうございます、泥建！
Congratulations, Doroken!

1138
02:13:29,885 --> 02:13:32,385
買いたかった... 泥建戻った！
I wanted to buy... Doroken is back!

1139
02:13:32,385 --> 02:13:35,885
ネネネ電鉄...
Nene Railway...

1140
02:13:35,885 --> 02:13:38,885
ネネ、ネネ、ネネ...
Nene, Nene, Nene...

1141
02:13:38,885 --> 02:13:40,885
おい、200円！
Hey, 200 yen!

1142
02:13:40,885 --> 02:13:43,385
ゼロ円？
Zero yen?

1143
02:13:43,385 --> 02:13:46,885
ゼロ円、ネネ電鉄。
Zero yen, Nene Railway.

1144
02:13:46,885 --> 02:13:49,385
おお...
Oh...

1145
02:13:49,385 --> 02:13:52,385
大空建設... ゼロ円だ！
Oozora Construction... Zero yen!

1146
02:13:52,385 --> 02:13:55,385
あ、大空建設は違う。
Ah, Oozora Construction is different.

1147
02:13:55,385 --> 02:13:58,385
これは戻れるか？
Can this recover?

1148
02:13:58,385 --> 02:14:01,385
プラス200円です！
Plus 200 yen!

1149
02:14:01,385 --> 02:14:04,385
さあ、最後。ねぽらぼホールディングス。
Now, the last one. Nepolabo Holdings.

1150
02:14:04,385 --> 02:14:07,885
これはちょっと...
This is a bit...

1151
02:14:07,885 --> 02:14:10,885
ねぽらぼ、ねぽらぼ...
Nepolabo, Nepolabo...

1152
02:14:10,885 --> 02:14:13,885
200！200！200！
200! 200! 200!

1153
02:14:13,885 --> 02:14:17,385
プラス200円！おめでとうございます！
Plus 200 yen! Congratulations!

1154
02:14:17,385 --> 02:14:20,385
以上！どうする？
That's all! What should we do?

1155
02:14:20,385 --> 02:14:22,885
上がった、上がった！
It went up, it went up!

1156
02:14:22,885 --> 02:14:26,385
わあ...
Wow...

1157
02:14:26,385 --> 02:14:29,385
わあ...
Wow...

1158
02:14:29,385 --> 02:14:32,385
200...

1159
02:14:32,385 --> 02:14:35,385
イナ、カブ...
Ina, stocks...

1160
02:14:35,385 --> 02:14:40,385
持ってない...持ってない...
I don't have... I don't have...

1161
02:14:40,385 --> 02:14:45,385
念のため... 念のためチェックしようか？
Just in case... Should I check just in case?

1162
02:14:45,385 --> 02:14:48,385
ここで...
Here...

1163
02:14:48,385 --> 02:14:51,385
うーん、どうしようかな...
Mmm, what should I do...

1164
02:14:51,385 --> 02:14:54,385
びび？びび？
Bibi? Bibi?

1165
02:14:54,385 --> 02:14:59,385
お前売るか？
Are you selling?

1166
02:15:00,966 --> 02:15:03,766
売る？でもみんな売ると安くなる。じゃ、やめて！
Sell? But if everyone sells, it gets cheaper. So stop!

1167
02:15:03,766 --> 02:15:05,166
うわー。
Wow...

1168
02:15:05,166 --> 02:15:06,466
こっち、ゼロ。
Zero on this side.

1169
02:15:06,466 --> 02:15:09,466
え、はよ売らんと...売るか？
Eh, sell it quickly... Sell it?

1170
02:15:09,466 --> 02:15:11,466
なんだよね。
Right?

1171
02:15:11,466 --> 02:15:13,466
売るか、売るか、売るか...
Are we selling, selling, selling...

1172
02:15:13,466 --> 02:15:15,266
所持金額100...
Money in possession: 100...

1173
02:15:15,266 --> 02:15:17,966
安っ！何これ高っ！安っ！
So cheap! What is this, so expensive! Cheap!

1174
02:15:20,466 --> 02:15:24,466
170円にしかなってないよとか言ってるから。いや、違う違う違う。
They're saying it's only 170 yen. No, no, no.

1175
02:15:24,466 --> 02:15:27,466
ありなのかな？オッケー。
Is that okay? Okay.

1176
02:15:27,466 --> 02:15:30,966
いや、カブとかさ...
No, the stocks...

1177
02:15:39,166 --> 02:15:42,166
みんなあんまわかんないから。
Because everyone doesn't really know.

1178
02:15:42,166 --> 02:15:47,466
Everyone bought Nepolabo.

1179
02:15:59,166 --> 02:16:00,966
My carrots.

1180
02:16:08,966 --> 02:16:12,466
Let's switch my bees back in.

1181
02:16:19,966 --> 02:16:21,966
Oh, yeah...

1182
02:16:21,966 --> 02:16:24,466
Oh, these also finished.

1183
02:16:33,466 --> 02:16:36,966
Ooh! Another Regen 2.

1184
02:16:43,466 --> 02:16:48,466
Well, I wanna finish eating my food.

1185
02:16:59,766 --> 02:17:11,966
Maybe you guys can stare at... dancing Inas while I eat. 'Cause I wanna eat before my food gets cold.

1186
02:17:11,966 --> 02:17:15,466
どこどこどこどこ...
Where, where, where, where...

1187
02:17:40,966 --> 02:17:45,166
Oh, Oozora was on a different server.

1188
02:17:46,966 --> 02:17:52,466
So the main one wouldn't go down. That's kind of smart, actually.

1189
02:17:55,966 --> 02:18:08,466
Ina is eating... Mic muted. There we go. I'll be right back!

1190
02:20:04,421 --> 02:25:04,421
INA IS EATING.. MIC MUTED!

1191
02:30:05,463 --> 02:30:10,463
Ina is eating... Mic muted!

1192
02:32:35,463 --> 02:32:38,963
Blegh! Hahaha.

1193
02:32:41,763 --> 02:32:45,463
My apologies, I was busy eating.

1194
02:32:47,263 --> 02:32:53,463
Nom nom nom nom nom...

1195
02:32:53,463 --> 02:32:55,963
That was yummy.

1196
02:33:04,963 --> 02:33:07,963
Hehehe.

1197
02:33:14,963 --> 02:33:18,963
Did the mic taste good? Oh wait, I forgot.

1198
02:33:29,263 --> 02:33:31,963
WO

1199
02:33:31,963 --> 02:33:33,963
sorry ate micro...

1200
02:33:33,963 --> 02:33:37,263
sorry ate microphone

1201
02:33:37,263 --> 02:33:39,663
can't speak

1202
02:33:39,663 --> 02:33:42,963
oh nyo

1203
02:34:04,963 --> 02:34:09,263
Ah, sorry guys, I pulled up my backup microphone.

1204
02:34:09,263 --> 02:34:10,963
No need to worry.

1205
02:34:10,963 --> 02:34:13,963
Hahaha.

1206
02:34:13,963 --> 02:34:18,663
Phew, good thing I have backups, you know?

1207
02:34:18,663 --> 02:34:22,963
Sometimes you just want to eat... you just want to eat some mics, you know?

1208
02:34:26,463 --> 02:34:30,963
And you have to make sure you eat them muted because they're going to scream if you don't.

1209
02:34:31,963 --> 02:34:34,463
You don't want your neighbors hearing that.

1210
02:34:35,963 --> 02:34:38,963
You don't want them to call the police.

1211
02:34:52,963 --> 02:34:55,963
Oh, I just had a great idea.

1212
02:35:02,463 --> 02:35:03,963
There we are, chat.

1213
02:35:07,684 --> 02:35:10,984
I don't know if it'll come to fruition, but I can try.

1214
02:35:27,684 --> 02:35:30,784
Oh, oh, my levels are gone because I died.

1215
02:35:30,784 --> 02:35:33,484
My twenty-something levels...

1216
02:35:55,984 --> 02:35:57,484
What is that? A bowl?

1217
02:36:04,984 --> 02:36:09,984
It's okay. If we can't repair the fishing rod, we'll just make a new one.

1218
02:36:10,784 --> 02:36:12,984
Tako. There you go.

1219
02:36:16,484 --> 02:36:20,484
Wait, we should have enough. I mean, we just have to get some sticks.

1220
02:36:26,684 --> 02:36:30,484
Started from the bottom, we're still here.

1221
02:36:37,984 --> 02:36:40,484
They're buying out stocks again?

1222
02:36:40,484 --> 02:36:44,984
They're... they're doing a... they're playing a dangerous game.

1223
02:36:49,284 --> 02:36:51,984
A very dangerous game.

1224
02:37:06,284 --> 02:37:08,284
Oh, not much salmon.

1225
02:37:08,984 --> 02:37:11,984
I feel like this happened before.

1226
02:37:12,484 --> 02:37:16,284
Where has this happened before? A faint memory.

1227
02:37:38,984 --> 02:37:41,284
One salmon.

1228
02:37:42,984 --> 02:37:45,984
Another time, another place.

1229
02:37:53,984 --> 02:37:56,984
Kabu... Haven't had turnips in a while.
Kabu [turnips]... Haven't had turnips in a while.

1230
02:37:57,284 --> 02:38:04,484
It's harder to have, like, different types of vegetables when you're in Japan,

1231
02:38:04,484 --> 02:38:07,484
which is why I eat cabbage a lot.

1232
02:38:07,484 --> 02:38:09,984
I'm sure there's a lot more, but like...

1233
02:38:10,484 --> 02:38:15,984
since I can't really cook for myself here, it's like I go to get the bagged salad and stuff,

1234
02:38:18,984 --> 02:38:24,984
but usually it's just like lettuce or cabbage with like some shredded carrots.

1235
02:38:24,984 --> 02:38:28,484
The very safe choices, you know, for salad.

1236
02:38:29,984 --> 02:38:35,484
I do find that, like, marts in America have more adventurous assortments of salads,

1237
02:38:35,484 --> 02:38:39,984
which I do appreciate... except the fact that they sell too much at once.

1238
02:38:45,984 --> 02:38:47,984
Oh, another salmon.

1239
02:38:54,984 --> 02:38:57,484
Like, the portions are a little too big.

1240
02:39:05,984 --> 02:39:12,984
Yeah, but then like, they go through the stock, like, in the marts and the conbini pretty fast, like, every day,
Yeah, but then like, they go through the stock, like, in the marts and the conbini [convenience store] pretty fast, like, every day,

1241
02:39:12,984 --> 02:39:16,984
so it does stay pretty fresh.

1242
02:39:18,484 --> 02:39:20,484
Which is the good part.

1243
02:39:25,484 --> 02:39:35,484
That's the thing because, like, I talked about this before, but like, marts in America, because the, you know, the land is so big,

1244
02:39:35,484 --> 02:39:39,984
everyone needs to drive to get to like a central location.

1245
02:39:39,984 --> 02:39:46,484
But since everyone lives in... like, the density of people in one area is so much higher in Japan,

1246
02:39:46,484 --> 02:39:52,484
there's so many smaller marts and convenience stores with fresh food you can get,

1247
02:39:52,484 --> 02:39:59,984
that you don't really need those bigger marts until you go out a little more into the rural areas.

1248
02:40:03,025 --> 02:40:04,425
A name tag.

1249
02:40:14,225 --> 02:40:16,025
I do, there's one...

1250
02:40:16,025 --> 02:40:18,525
Oh, veggie... uh...

1251
02:40:18,525 --> 02:40:21,525
Number of shares circulating in Holotown. As a result,

1252
02:40:21,525 --> 02:40:23,625
while selling still decreases...

1253
02:40:23,625 --> 02:40:27,025
the stock price, the fluctuations are much smaller than before. Thank you for your understanding.

1254
02:40:27,325 --> 02:40:28,525
Aha.

1255
02:40:30,425 --> 02:40:32,025
What are they talking about?

1256
02:40:33,225 --> 02:40:38,325
Oh, yeah. Well, one of the veggies that I really, really like grilled, actually,

1257
02:40:39,025 --> 02:40:41,225
is Brussels sprouts.

1258
02:40:42,125 --> 02:40:48,325
I really like grilled Brussels sprouts. Just, nothing fancy, just a little bit of oil...

1259
02:40:48,325 --> 02:40:50,325
...little bit of salt and pepper.

1260
02:40:51,325 --> 02:40:54,525
Mmm, Brussels sprouts.

1261
02:40:57,425 --> 02:41:00,625
I love grilled veggies in general. Grilled veggies are delicious.

1262
02:41:08,425 --> 02:41:13,525
That's the one thing I miss, I guess. Like, the barbecue-grilled vegetables.

1263
02:41:15,725 --> 02:41:18,625
Like, even when, like, our family would have a barbecue...

1264
02:41:18,625 --> 02:41:21,625
...in the backyard, I would only really be like...

1265
02:41:21,625 --> 02:41:24,225
...eating the veggies...

1266
02:41:26,025 --> 02:41:28,125
...and then a bit of meat here and there.

1267
02:41:29,525 --> 02:41:34,725
Nothing beats like actual barbecue with grilled...

1268
02:41:34,725 --> 02:41:36,225
...veggies.

1269
02:41:37,025 --> 02:41:39,025
Mmm.

1270
02:41:49,025 --> 02:41:54,825
I think really good grilled vegetables don't need sauce, just a little bit of salt.

1271
02:41:55,225 --> 02:41:58,225
Honestly, I don't even need salt sometimes, because...

1272
02:41:58,225 --> 02:42:01,225
...a good grilled vegetable has its own like...

1273
02:42:01,225 --> 02:42:03,625
...umami, you know?

1274
02:42:04,025 --> 02:42:06,025
Its own flavor.

1275
02:42:07,225 --> 02:42:09,025
Its own sweetness.

1276
02:42:19,125 --> 02:42:20,525
Yeah.

1277
02:42:32,025 --> 02:42:35,425
And that's the one thing, I guess, I kind of miss about...

1278
02:42:35,425 --> 02:42:36,825
...summer...

1279
02:42:37,025 --> 02:42:38,825
...and our family being...

1280
02:42:38,825 --> 02:42:42,525
...all across the world, is the summer barbecues.

1281
02:42:43,425 --> 02:42:45,125
And eating...

1282
02:42:46,025 --> 02:42:48,325
...outside in the backyard.

1283
02:42:51,325 --> 02:42:53,125
Like, mama Ina...

1284
02:42:53,125 --> 02:42:54,525
...likes gardening,

1285
02:42:54,525 --> 02:42:58,825
so our backyard used to look so beautiful.

1286
02:42:59,825 --> 02:43:03,025
Plus there were a lot of mosquitoes and bees, but...

1287
02:43:03,025 --> 02:43:04,825
...which is the part I didn't like.

1288
02:43:05,025 --> 02:43:08,425
But, it was still so, so pretty when the flowers bloomed.

1289
02:43:09,025 --> 02:43:11,525
It literally looked like...

1290
02:43:11,525 --> 02:43:14,825
...a garden out of, like, a Ghibli movie.

1291
02:43:14,825 --> 02:43:17,525
I was like, "Wow, it's so beautiful!" Oh, a stick!

1292
02:43:20,625 --> 02:43:25,025
One less stick needed to make the next fishing rod.

1293
02:43:31,025 --> 02:43:34,525
Speaking of mosquitoes, I got bitten yesterday.

1294
02:43:35,425 --> 02:43:37,525
I got bitten yesterday, I was like, "Ah..."

1295
02:43:37,525 --> 02:43:41,225
"...this year's first mosquito bite, I see."

1296
02:43:47,025 --> 02:43:50,425
My first donation of blood...

1297
02:43:51,025 --> 02:43:54,025
...to my mortal enemies.

1298
02:44:02,825 --> 02:44:05,825
Oh, it switched. It changed to suika.
Oh, it switched. It changed to watermelon.

1299
02:44:14,325 --> 02:44:19,125
But then like, I kind of like had a feeling I would get a mosquito bite there...

1300
02:44:19,325 --> 02:44:20,825
Oh, more shoes!

1301
02:44:21,525 --> 02:44:24,025
...'cause like, it was kind of in like a shaded area...

1302
02:44:24,025 --> 02:44:27,025
...beside a bunch of plants, I was like...

1303
02:44:27,025 --> 02:44:30,225
"I'm going to get a mosquito bite, aren't I?"

1304
02:44:30,225 --> 02:44:32,025
And then I did.

1305
02:44:36,225 --> 02:44:38,025
I just had that feeling.

1306
02:44:42,025 --> 02:44:45,525
I used to be like so much... I think it's a little less now.

1307
02:44:46,025 --> 02:44:51,325
Maybe it's returned a little bit, but I used to be so like, almost allergic to mosquito bites.

1308
02:44:52,025 --> 02:44:53,025
To a point where, like...

1309
02:44:53,025 --> 02:44:56,025
Ah! It broke! But a saddle!

1310
02:44:57,025 --> 02:44:59,025
I don't have a horse.

1311
02:45:00,633 --> 02:45:01,933
I like this one, too.

1312
02:45:06,633 --> 02:45:13,633
And then they swell so much, no matter how much I do, how much ice packs and medicine I put on it, it would swell so much.

1313
02:45:21,133 --> 02:45:28,633
But then, surprisingly enough, there was a... there was a time I wasn't as like, healthy, I guess?

1314
02:45:28,733 --> 02:45:32,133
And then, I never really got that many mosquito bites then.

1315
02:45:33,633 --> 02:45:36,633
And I was like, "These mosquitoes..."

1316
02:45:37,133 --> 02:45:42,133
They're... they're smart.

1317
02:45:42,133 --> 02:45:45,633
They know when the prey is not yummy.

1318
02:45:45,633 --> 02:45:47,633
How did they know?

1319
02:45:53,633 --> 02:45:59,633
Like they would fly by, and they'd be like, "Ugh, ugh, disgusting." And they'd just fly off.

1320
02:46:00,633 --> 02:46:05,133
What's happening? How can I return to that state?

1321
02:46:05,633 --> 02:46:08,633
Ah, another saddle. But I don't have a horse.

1322
02:46:09,133 --> 02:46:12,133
Okay, we must get stick.

1323
02:46:13,633 --> 02:46:17,633
Wait, are we even going to get 1,000...

1324
02:46:17,633 --> 02:46:21,633
...by the deadline? I don't know,

1325
02:46:21,633 --> 02:46:24,133
I'm not... I'm not too confident right now.

1326
02:46:24,633 --> 02:46:28,133
Wait, do I get money if I break leaves? I don't.

1327
02:46:30,133 --> 02:46:34,133
Give me stick. Give me more stick.

1328
02:46:39,633 --> 02:46:45,133
All these woods will be barren when I'm done with it.

1329
02:46:47,133 --> 02:46:50,633
I guess it doesn't really make a difference. Give me stick!

